            "img": "systems/sf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
            "name": "Necrotic Transmission",
            "sort": 700000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A creature that takes damage from a necrolinked wight's Shriek must succeed at a @Check[will|dc:15] save, or its subconscious is scanned and used to infect its non-augmentation tech items with a virus. Infected tech items display algorithmically generated content catering specifically to the creature's deepest desires, causing the creature to become @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.Off-Guard] as long as they're holding or wearing the tech item. On a critical failure, the creature is also @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.Fascinated], and all creatures and objects other than the tech item are @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.Concealed] from the creature. The creature or its allies can end the effect on any specific tech item by Interacting to reboot the affected item and succeeding at a @Check[computers|dc:15] check; on a failure, the item becomes glitching 1 (glitching 2 on a critical failure).</p>"
                },
